[2]
Date: 8 Sep 2010
Source: Google/AFP [edited]
<http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iHMbYbZeMY406zo2lDM9fGWowvOg>


Bangladesh anthrax spreads ahead of Eid
---------------------------------------
Bangladesh has set up anthrax checkpoints at cattle markets as a major
outbreak of the disease spreads through the country's dairy belt, infecting
more than 400 people, officials said on Wednesday [8 Sep 2010].

A total of 8 districts have confirmed human and cattle anthrax infections.
Meat consumption ahead of the Islamic festival of Eid, set to start Friday
[10 Sep 2010], has fallen sharply as panicked consumers have turned their
backs on beef, officials said.

The authorities have set up checkpoints across the country in an effort to
prevent diseased meat reaching the capital Dhaka, said livestock department
deputy director Mosaddek Hossain. "We have sent vets to markets to screen
animals. We want to calm the public down. Already meat consumption has
declined sharply as panicky consumers are avoiding beef," he said.

